3. DEPARTMENTS COMPLETED SUMMARY
==================================================

Important wording:
Use “Departments Completed”, not “Work Order Closure”.

Do not use:
- Work Order Closure
- Work Order Closure totals
- Work Order Closure summary
- Work Order Closure performance summary

Use:
- Departments Completed
- Departments Completed totals
- Departments Completed summary

Purpose:
Departments Completed is the dashboard completion/status summary for all handover departments.

It answers:
“How many handover sections are Complete, Incomplete, or Not running?”

Departments Completed uses all departments:
1. Injection
2. MetaPress
3. Berks
4. Wilts
5. Racking
6. Butchery
7. Further Processing
8. Tumblers
9. Smoke Tumbler
10. Minimums & Samples
11. Goods In & Despatch
12. Dry Goods
13. Additional

Status values:
- Complete
- Incomplete
- Not running

Example display:

Departments Completed
- Complete: 8
- Incomplete: 2
- Not running: 3
- Total departments: 13

Optional display:
- Completion: 8 / 13 departments complete

Important:
Departments Completed is separate from metric performance.

Departments Completed:
- uses all departments
- based only on department status

Metric Summary:
- uses only Injection, MetaPress, Berks, Wilts
- based on downtime, efficiency, yield


==================================================
4. SHIFT / SESSION SCREEN
==================================================

Purpose:
The Shift / Session screen is the entry point into the app.

It lets the user choose:
- shift
- date
- user

It then opens an existing session or creates a blank session after confirmation.

Must show:
- app title: MOAT HOUSE HANDOVER
- instruction text
- shift selector:
  - AM
  - PM
  - NS
- date selector:
  - default to today
  - allow past/future dates
- user name field:
  - default to current Windows/user where possible
  - editable if needed
- Open Session button
- Diagnostics button
- message/status area

Open Session behaviour:
- read ShiftCode, ShiftDate, UserName
- call session.open
- if session exists:
  - load session
  - set active session in app state
  - navigate to Dashboard
- if session does not exist:
  - show confirmation:
    “No session exists for this shift/date. Create a blank session?”
  - if confirmed:
    - call session.createBlank
    - navigate to Dashboard
  - if cancelled:
    - stay on Shift screen

Diagnostics button:
- opens Diagnostics screen
- Diagnostics must work before any active session exists

Validation:
- shift is required
- date is required
- user name should not crash if blank; use fallback where possible

Must not:
- create session without user confirmation
- clear/delete session
- open Dashboard without valid active session


