Dashboard actions:
- Open Department
- Open Budget
- Open Preview
- Open Send
- Clear Day
- Diagnostics
- Back to Shift

Open Department:
- selected department is passed to Department View
- Department View loads saved data for session + department

Open Budget:
- opens Budget View for active session

Open Preview:
- opens read-only Preview from saved data

Open Send:
- opens Send View / package preparation

Clear Day:
- must show strong confirmation
- resets current shift/date session data only
- resets department status/notes/metric values according to clear-day rules
- should refresh Dashboard after completion
- should write audit entry

Diagnostics:
- opens Diagnostics screen

Must not:
- edit detailed department data directly on Dashboard
- use “Work Order Closure” wording
- calculate Departments Completed from only metric departments
- calculate Metric Summary from non-metric departments
- generate reports automatically
- send email automatically


==================================================
6. DEPARTMENT HANDOVER VIEW
==================================================

Purpose:
Department View is where the user enters handover information for one selected department.

Header should show:
- Department name
- ShiftCode
- ShiftDate
- SessionId
- whether department is metric or non-metric

Common fields for all departments:
- Status:
  - Not running
  - Complete
  - Incomplete
- Notes
- Attachments

Metric fields only for:
- Injection
- MetaPress
- Berks
- Wilts

Metric fields:
- Downtime minutes
- Efficiency %
- Yield %

Metric department form should show:
- Status
- Downtime
- Efficiency %
- Yield %
- Notes
- Attachments

Non-metric department form should show:
- Status
- Notes
- Attachments

Non-metric department form must hide:
- Downtime
- Efficiency %
- Yield %

Default values:
- Status: Not running
- Notes: blank
- Metric values: blank
- Attachments: existing saved list or empty

Buttons:
- Save
- Add Attachment
- Remove Attachment
- View Attachment
- Previous Attachment
- Next Attachment
- Back to Dashboard

Save behaviour:
- save department status
- save notes
- save metrics only for metric departments
- save updated at/by
- audit: department.save
- refresh dashboard when returning

Validation:
- status required
- downtime numeric and not negative if entered
- efficiency numeric if entered
- yield numeric if entered
- blank metrics allowed where appropriate
- notes can be blank
- invalid input shows clear message, not crash

Attachment panel:
Must show:
- attachment list
- selected attachment metadata
- attachment count
- thumbnail/preview if supported
- clear message if preview cannot load

Add Attachment:
- open file picker
- copy selected file to managed AttachmentsRoot
- save metadata in Access
- preserve original display name
- refresh list/count
- audit: attachment.add

Remove Attachment:
- soft-delete metadata
- do not physically delete file by default
- clear stale preview
- refresh list/count
- audit: attachment.remove

Previous/Next Attachment:
- changes selected attachment
- updates preview
- updates metadata
- must not leave old image shown

View Attachment:
- opens selected attachment in Image Viewer
- viewer uses managed path only

Must not:
- show metric fields for non-metric departments
- save metrics for non-metric departments
- embed attachments in Access
- use unmanaged original path as permanent storage
- leave stale thumbnail after removal/navigation


==================================================
7. IMAGE VIEWER
==================================================

Purpose:
Image Viewer shows selected department attachment larger than the Department View thumbnail.

Must show:
- selected attachment display name
- department name
- captured/uploaded date
- current index, e.g. 1 of 3
- image/file preview
- Previous
- Next
- Close/Back

Data source:
- active session
- selected department
- selected attachment
- managed attachment list

Behaviour:
- Previous changes selected attachment
- Next changes selected attachment
- image updates
- metadata updates
- missing file shows clear message
- unsupported preview shows clear message

Image display:
- maintain aspect ratio
- fit to viewer area
- be larger than Department thumbnail
- readable quality
- do not stretch badly

