==================================================
8. BUDGET VIEW
==================================================

Purpose:
Budget View tracks planned staff vs used staff for the active shift/date/session.

Budget is about labour/headcount, not production metrics.

Budget is separate from:
- downtime
- efficiency
- yield
- metric summary

Budget applies to all departments/areas, not only metric departments.

Budget should load by:
- SessionId
- ShiftCode
- ShiftDate

Budget row departments should follow the department list unless future budget templates override it:
1. Injection
2. MetaPress
3. Berks
4. Wilts
5. Racking
6. Butchery
7. Further Processing
8. Tumblers
9. Smoke Tumbler
10. Minimums & Samples
11. Goods In & Despatch
12. Dry Goods
13. Additional

Budget row fields:
- Department / area
- Planned staff
- Used staff
- Variance
- Reason / notes
- Status

Variance:
Variance = Used - Planned

Examples:
Planned 10, Used 12 = +2 Over
Planned 10, Used 8 = -2 Under
Planned 10, Used 10 = 0 On target

Budget status:
- On target
- Over
- Under
- Not set

Budget summary should show:
- planned total
- used total
- variance total
- overall status
- row count
- last updated

Buttons:
- Save Budget
- Recalculate
- Back to Dashboard
- optionally Preview

Save Budget:
- save rows to Access
- save updated at/by
- recalculate totals
- refresh Dashboard Budget Summary
- audit: budget.save

Recalculate:
- recalculates row variance
- recalculates totals
- should work before save
- should not corrupt data

Validation:
- planned cannot be negative
- used cannot be negative
- blank numeric values handled consistently
- variance is calculated, not manually typed
- reason/notes can be blank
- invalid row shows clear message

Must not:
- mix budget variance with efficiency/yield/downtime
- show budget only for metric departments
- generate reports automatically
- send email
- use fake hardcoded values when persistence exists


