Preview must load from persisted saved state.

It must not use unsaved UI state.

Must show session header:
- ShiftCode
- ShiftDate
- SessionId
- SessionStatus
- Created at/by
- Updated at/by

Must show Departments Completed:
- Complete count
- Incomplete count
- Not running count
- Total departments
- completion ratio if useful

Must show department summary:
For each department:
- Department name
- Status
- Notes
- Attachment count
- Updated at/by

For metric departments only:
- Downtime
- Efficiency %
- Yield %

Must show Metric Summary:
- downtime total
- average efficiency
- average yield
- based only on Injection, MetaPress, Berks, Wilts

Must show Budget Summary:
- planned total
- used total
- variance total
- budget status

Must show Budget Rows:
- department
- planned
- used
- variance
- reason

Must show attachment summary:
- attachment counts by department
- optionally display names

Buttons:
- Back to Dashboard
- Generate Handover Report
- Generate Budget Report
- Generate Both Reports
- Open Reports Folder
- Go to Send / Prepare Send Package

Preview is read-only:
- no editing department
- no editing budget
- no attachment add/remove
- no automatic send

Must not:
- modify data while loading
- generate from unsaved UI state
- send email
- create Outlook draft automatically


==================================================
10. REPORTS
==================================================

Purpose:
Reports are generated local files created from saved session data.

Reports are not the same as Preview.

Preview = on-screen read-only view.
Reports = output files.

Report types:
1. Handover report
2. Budget report
3. Optional combined report if implemented

Reports are saved under:
- ReportsRoot

Handover report should include:
- shift/date/session header
- Departments Completed summary
- department statuses
- department notes
- metric values for Injection, MetaPress, Berks, Wilts
- Metric Summary
- attachment counts
- generated at/by

Budget report should include:
- shift/date/session header
- planned total
- used total
- variance total
- budget status
- budget rows
- generated at/by

File naming examples:
- Handover_AM_2026-04-29_Session123.html
- Budget_AM_2026-04-29_Session123.html

Rules:
- use persisted saved state
- escape user-entered text
- no unsafe raw HTML from notes/reasons
- return generated file paths to UI
- audit report generation

Audit:
- reports.generateHandover
- reports.generateBudget
- reports.generateAll

Must not:
- generate from unsaved UI state
- require Office automation
- require cloud service
- require local web server
- send email automatically


==================================================
11. SEND / OUTLOOK DRAFT VIEW
==================================================

Purpose:
Send View prepares an email package and creates an Outlook draft only.

It must never automatically send an email.

Must show:
- session info
- email profile key
- To recipients
- CC recipients
- subject preview
- body preview
- report attachment paths
- validation messages
- readiness status

Buttons:
- Prepare Package
- Create Outlook Draft
- Back to Preview
- Back to Dashboard

Prepare Package:
- load active session
- load email profile by shift
- generate or reuse handover report
- generate or reuse budget report
- confirm report paths exist
- build subject from template
- build body from template
- return package payload
- audit: send.preparePackage

Create Outlook Draft:
- requires prepared package
- attempts Outlook COM draft creation
- sets To / CC / Subject / Body
- attaches reports
- does not send
- returns success/failure
- audit: send.createOutlookDraft

Validation messages:
- session missing
- reports missing
- report generation failed
- email profile missing
- email profile inactive
- no recipients
- Outlook unavailable
- file path missing
- attachment/report path not found

Must not:
- send automatically
- include Send Now button
- use SMTP
- use cloud email
- hide validation errors
- claim draft success unless host confirms it


==================================================
12. DIAGNOSTICS SCREEN
==================================================

Purpose:
Diagnostics checks whether the app can run correctly on the current machine.

It must work before a shift session is opened.

Must show:
- Runtime Diagnostics title
- Run Diagnostics first guidance
- Windows/WebView2/ACE/Outlook boundary message

Buttons:
- Run Diagnostics
- Refresh Audit
- Open Logs Folder
- Back to Dashboard
- Back to Shift

Must show overall status:
- OK
- Warning
- Failed

Must show runtime paths:
- Config file
- Access DB path
- Attachments root
- Reports root
- Logs root
- Asset root

Diagnostics checks:
- OS / Windows runtime
- config loaded
- Access DB path exists
- Access connection opens
- tblConfig seed
- Attachments folder exists/can be created
- Attachments folder write access
- Reports folder exists/can be created
- Reports folder write access
- Logs folder exists
- Email profile mappings exist for AM/PM/NS
- Active email profiles valid
- Outlook COM availability
- Runtime boundary check

Each check row should show:
- check name
- status
- message
- details

Open Logs Folder:
- host opens log folder if possible
- failure shown clearly

Refresh Audit:
- if session exists, show audit for session
- if no session exists, show recent audit entries

Must not:
- require active session
- create Outlook draft
- send email
- modify business data
- crash because one diagnostic check failed


==================================================
13. AUDIT LOG
==================================================

Purpose:
Audit log records important workflow actions.

Audit logging must be best-effort:
- if audit fails, workflow continues
- audit failure is logged where possible
- audit failure does not block save/report/send operations

Audit row fields:
- AuditId
- EventAt
- UserName
- EntityType
- EntityKey
- ActionType
- Details

Actions to audit:
- session.open
- session.createBlank
- session.clearDay
- department.save
- attachment.add
- attachment.remove
- budget.save
- reports.generateHandover
- reports.generateBudget
- reports.generateAll
- send.preparePackage
- send.createOutlookDraft result

Audit display:
- Diagnostics screen shows recent entries
- Entries show action/time/entity/user/details

Must not:
- store huge sensitive email body text unnecessarily
- crash main workflow if audit fails


==================================================
14. ATTACHMENT STORAGE RULES
==================================================

Purpose:
Attachments are evidence/files/images linked to department handover.

Storage:
- files copied to managed AttachmentsRoot
- Access stores metadata only
- original display name preserved
- managed file path stored
- linked to session + department

Metadata:
- AttachmentId
- SessionId
- DeptRecordId
- DeptName
- DisplayName
- ManagedFilePath
- CapturedOn
- SequenceNo
- IsDeleted

Remove:
- soft-delete metadata
- physical delete deferred unless approved later

Viewer:
- only managed files under AttachmentsRoot
- no arbitrary file paths

Must not:
- embed files in Access
- rely on original source file path permanently
- delete physical files by default
- show stale preview


==================================================
15. DATA STORAGE RULES
==================================================

Structured data:
- Access database

File data:
- AttachmentsRoot
- ReportsRoot
- LogsRoot

Runtime config:
- defines database path
- defines attachments path
- defines reports path
- supports logs/config path where applicable

Do not:
- replace Access
- add local web server
- store attachments in Access
- store reports in Access


==================================================
16. STATUS RULES
==================================================

Department statuses:
- Not running
- Complete
- Incomplete

Default department status:
- Not running

Department status meaning:
- Not running = department/line did not run
- Complete = section completed
- Incomplete = issue/open item remains

Budget statuses:
- On target
- Over
- Under
- Not set

Diagnostics statuses:
- ok
- warning
- failed

Send package statuses:
- ready
- not ready
- warning where useful


==================================================
17. NEVER-DO RULES
==================================================

Never:
- do not use “Work Order Closure” wording
- do not send email automatically
- do not add Send Now
- do not use SMTP/cloud email
- do not replace Access
- do not add local web server
- do not store attachments inside database
- do not show downtime/efficiency/yield for non-metric departments
- do not calculate Departments Completed from metric departments only
- do not calculate Metric Summary from non-metric departments
- do not generate reports from unsaved UI state
- do not create Outlook draft without user action
- do not claim Windows runtime is verified unless tested on real Windows
- do not hide validation failures
- do not mark failed bridge calls as success
- do not overbuild future stages early
Key updated concept:
Departments Completed = status summary for all 13 departments. Metric Summary = downtime / efficiency / yield only for Injection, MetaPress, Berks, Wilts.
